column5: I have read a great deal of Nf and thought some would like to see my passion. I fished with my mate gary on the weekend a very tough weekend. Many follows one takers lost by Gary at boat on Saturday but no other takers, finally sunday morning when you only have an hour you catch straight away. Another nice solid fish for 2011. Thanks to everyone who has fished with me this year it has been awesome and sorry for the sore shoulders. The first year that I spent casting the majority of time with zero on the troll!
Well done John. Fish of a thousand casts and a beauty!  p.-
way to go...  it takes drive to cast all day in november...
Nice clean fish!!! Congrats on sticking it out this late, it isnt easy!
Good Job John sounds like a great season for you this year.Next year we will have you back down here and get you a LSC musky.
Really nice musky! Persistence pays off.
I'll forgive you for the sore shoulder!
